obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (40346)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00018_196130_1517807324533&sectionId=40346&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00018_196130_1517807324533
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Delhi (Urban Areas)`
  line `Tenant's Relief Act, 1961.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the areas in the Union territory of Delhi which, immediately before the`
  line `1st day of November, 1956, were included in a municipality or in a notified area under the provisions of`
  line `the Punjab Municipal Act, 1911 (Punjab Act 3 of 1911), or in a cantonment under the provisions of the`
  line `Cantonments Act, 1924 (2 of 1924), but shall not apply to the areas owned by the Central Government or`
  line `the Delhi Development Authority constituted under the Delhi Development Act, 1957 (61 of 1957), or`
  line `any local authority.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date as the Chief Commissioner may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (40347)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00018_196130_1517807324533&sectionId=40347&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00018_196130_1517807324533
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Chief Commissioner" means the Chief Commissioner of Delhi;`
  line
  line `(b) "family" means--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to a person belonging to a joint Hindu family, every member of such`
  line `family; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to any other person, the person, the wife or husband, as the case may be, and`
  line `the dependent children and grand-children, of such person;`
  line
  line `(c) "land-holder" means a person under whom a tenant holds land and to whom the tenant is, or`
  line `but for a special contract would be, liable to pay rent for the land;`
  line
  line `(d) "person under disability" means,--`
  line
  line `(i) a widow;`
  line
  line `(ii) a minor whose father has died;`
  line
  line `(iii) a woman who is unmarried or who, if married, is divorced or judicially separated from`
  line `her husband or whose husband is a person falling under item (iv) or (v);`
  line
  line `(iv) a member of the Armed Forces of the Union;`
  line
  line `(v) a person incapable of cultivating land by reason of some physical or mental disability;`
  line
  line `(vi) a person prosecuting studies in a recognised institution and not exceeding 25 years of`
  line `age; or`
  line
  line `(vii) a person who is under detention or undergoing imprisonment;`
  line
  line `(e) "tenant" and "tenancy" include a sub-tenant and a sub-tenancy respectively;`
  line
  line `(f) the words "land" and "tenant" and all other words and expressions used but not defined in this`
  line `Act and defined in the Punjab Tenancy Act, 1887 (16 of 1887), or the Agra Tenancy Act, 1901`
  line `(U.P. Act II of 1901), shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them,--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to areas to which the Punjab Tenancy Act, 1887 (16 of 1887), applies, in that`
  line `Act; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to areas to which the Agra Tenancy Act, 1901 (U.P. Act II of 1901), applies, in`
  line `that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (40348)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Grounds of ejectment of tenant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00018_196130_1517807324533&sectionId=40348&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00018_196130_1517807324533
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) After the commencement of this Act, no person shall be`
  line `liable to be ejected from any land held by him as tenant except on one or more of the following`
  line `grounds, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) that a decree for arrear of rent due in respect of the land remains unsatisfied after the expiry of`
  line `the period allowed therefor;`
  line
  line `(b) where rent is payable in kind, that he has without sufficient cause failed to cultivate the land;`
  line
  line `(c) that he has sub-let or otherwise transferred the whole or any part of the tenancy in`
  line `contravention of any law for the time being in force or of any contract;`
  line
  line `(d) that he has used the land in a manner which renders it unfit for the purpose for which it`
  line `was let.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1) but subject to the provisions of any law for`
  line `the time being in force or of any contract between the parties, a tenant may be ejected from the land held`
  line `by him by a land-holder,--`
  line
  line `(a) in any case where the land-holder is a religious or charitable institution, on the ground that the`
  line `institution requires the land bona fide for use for a non-agricultural purpose in furtherance of its`
  line `objects; and`
  line
  line `(b) in any case where the land-holder was a person under disability at the commencement of the`
  line `tenancy, on the ground that he requires the land bona fide for cultivation by himself or for building a`
  line `dwelling house, a cattle shed or business premises for use by himself or any member of his family and`
  line `the proceeding for ejectment is instituted during the period when he is under disability or within two`
  line `years from the date when he cases or has ceased to be under disability:`
  line
  line `Provided that no proceeding shall lie under this sub-section in respect of any share of land unless the`
  line `share has first been partitioned by metes and bounds.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, the disability of a person shall cease,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a widow, if she re-marries, on the date of her re-marriage or if any person`
  line `succeeds to the widow on her death, on the date of her death;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a minor, on the date of his attaining majority;`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of a woman who is unmarried or who is divorced or judicially separated from her`
  line `husband, on the date of her marriage or re-marriage, as the case may be, or in the case of a woman`
  line `whose husband is a person falling under clause (d) or (e), on the date on which the disability of the`
  line `husband ceases;`
  line
  line `(d) in the case of a person who is a member of the Armed Forces of the Union, on the date of his`
  line `discharge from service or of his posting to the reserve;`
  line
  line `(e) in the case of a person suffering from a physical or mental disability, on the date on which the`
  line `disability ceases to exist;`
  line
  line `(f) in the case of a person who is prosecuting studies in a recognised institution, on the date when`
  line `he ceases to prosecute studies in that or any other recognised institution;`
  line
  line `(g) in the case of a person under detention or undergoing imprisonment, on the date when he is`
  line `released from detention or imprisonment.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (40349)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Abatement of proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00018_196130_1517807324533&sectionId=40349&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00018_196130_1517807324533
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Save as provided in section 3, no tenant of land shall, whether in`
  line `execution of a decree or order of a court or otherwise, be ejected from the land, and if there is any`
  line `proceeding for ejectment of such tenant pending immediately before the commencement of this Act and`
  line `the proceeding could not have been instituted had this Act been in force at the time of the institution of`
  line `such proceeding, then, notwithstanding anything contained in any law, such proceeding shall, on such`
  line `commencement, abate.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (40350)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Restoration of land to tenant in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00018_196130_1517807324533&sectionId=40350&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00018_196130_1517807324533
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, after the commencement of this Act,`
  line `a person under disability or a religious or charitable institution has taken possession of land by ejecting`
  line `the tenant therefrom under sub-section (2) of section 3 on the ground that the land is required for a`
  line `purpose specified in that sub-section and such person or institution fails to use the land for that purpose`
  line `within one year from the date on which such person or institution took possession thereof, the tenant shall`
  line `be entitled to be restored to possession of the land from which he was ejected, on the same terms on`
  line `which he held it at the time of ejectment.`
  line
  line `(2) Where, on or after the 1st July, 1958 and before the commencement of this Act, any tenant of land`
  line `has been ejected from the land and the ejectment could not have taken place if this Act had been in force`
  line `on the date of such ejectment, the officer specified in this behalf by the Chief Commissioner may, either`
  line `on his own motion or on application made by the tenant, restore him to possession of the land from which`
  line `he has been ejected, on the same terms on which he held it at the time of ejectment.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section shall be construed as entitling a tenant to be restored to possession of any`
  line `land if it is under cultivation by the owner who is a person under disability or has, on or before the`
  line `28th day of March, 1961, ceased to be used for agricultural purposes.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (40351)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title Rent.
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00018_196130_1517807324533&sectionId=40351&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00018_196130_1517807324533
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The rent payable by a tenant in respect of land held by him as such shall not exceed`
  line `one-fifth of the produce of the land or the money equivalent thereof, or where a lower rent is agreed upon`
  line `between him and the land-holder, the agreed rent.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (40352)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Act to override contracts, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00018_196130_1517807324533&sectionId=40352&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00018_196130_1517807324533
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall, save as otherwise expressly`
  line `provided, have effect notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any other law, custom or`
  line `usage or agreement or decree or order of court.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (40353)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00018_196130_1517807324533&sectionId=40353&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00018_196130_1517807324533
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief Commissioner may, by notification in the official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made under this section be laid as soon as may be after it is made, before each House`
  line `of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session`
  line `or in two successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session in which it is so laid or the session`
  line `immediately following, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree`
  line `that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of`
  line `no effect, as the case may be, so however that any such modification or annulment shall be without`
  line `prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (40354)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title Repeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00018_196130_1517807324533&sectionId=40354&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00018_196130_1517807324533
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of the Punjab Tenancy Act, 1887 (16 of 1887), and the Agra Tenancy`
  line `U.P. Act, 1901 (U.P. Act II of 1901), and the Punjab Tenants (Security of Tenure)`
  line `Act, 1950, (Punjab Act XXII of 1950) as applicable to the areas to which this Act extends, which are`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act are hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken in exercise of any power`
  line `conferred by or under any of the provisions so repealed, to the extent to which it is not inconsistent with`
  line `the provisions of this Act, shall be deemed to have been done or taken in exercise of the powers conferred`
  line `by this Act as if this Act was in force on the date on which such thing was done or such action was taken.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
